  "chapter": {
    "number": 59,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Sin Separates Us from God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely the arm of the LORD is not too short to save,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor His ear too dull to hear.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But your iniquities have built barriers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "between you and your God,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and your sins have hidden His face from you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that He does not hear.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For your hands are stained with blood,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your fingers with iniquity;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "your lips have spoken lies,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your tongue mutters injustice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No one calls for justice;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no one pleads his case honestly.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They rely on empty pleas; they tell lies;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they conceive mischief and give birth to iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They hatch the eggs of vipers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and weave a spider’s web.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Whoever eats their eggs will die;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "crack one open, and a viper is hatched.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their cobwebs cannot be made into clothing,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they cannot cover themselves with their works.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Their deeds are sinful deeds,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and acts of violence are in their hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their feet run to evil;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are swift to shed innocent blood.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Their thoughts are sinful thoughts;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "ruin and destruction",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2718
          },
          {
            "text": "lie in their wake.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The way of peace they have not known,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2719
          },
          {
            "text": "and there is no justice in their tracks.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They have turned them into crooked paths;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no one who treads on them will know peace.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore justice is far from us,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and righteousness does not reach us.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "We hope for light, but there is darkness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for brightness, but we walk in gloom.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like the blind, we feel our way along the wall,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "groping like those without eyes.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "We stumble at midday as in the twilight;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "among the vigorous we are like the dead.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We all growl like bears",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and moan like doves.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "We hope for justice, but find none,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for salvation, but it is far from us.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For our transgressions are multiplied before You,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and our sins testify against us.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Our transgressions are indeed with us,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and we know our iniquities:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "rebelling and denying the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "turning away from our God,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "speaking oppression and revolt,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "conceiving and uttering lies from the heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So justice is turned away,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and righteousness stands at a distance.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For truth has stumbled in the public square,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and honesty cannot enter.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Truth is missing,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and whoever turns from evil becomes prey.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD looked and was displeased",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2720
          },
          {
            "text": "that there was no justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He saw that there was no man;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He was amazed that there was no one to intercede.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So His own arm brought salvation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and His own righteousness sustained Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He put on righteousness like a breastplate,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the helmet of salvation on His head;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He put on garments of vengeance",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wrapped Himself in a cloak of zeal.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Covenant of the Redeemer"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So He will repay according to their deeds:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "fury to His enemies,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "retribution to His foes,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and recompense to the islands.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2721
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So shall they fear the name of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "where the sun sets,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and His glory where it rises.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For He will come like a raging flood,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "driven by the breath of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2722
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“The Redeemer will come to Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to those in Jacob who turn from transgression,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2723
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "“As for Me, this is My covenant with them,”",
          {
            "noteId": 2724
          },
          "says the LORD. “My Spirit will not depart from you,",
          {
            "noteId": 2725
          },
          "and My words that I have put in your mouth will not depart from your mouth or from the mouths of your children and grandchildren, from now on and forevermore,” says the LORD."
        ]
      }
    ],
